The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   BRIEFS
                  
	Calcutta, June 21: A young housewife who was admitted to Medical College Hospital with epilepsy showed burn- like symptoms after a suspected drug reaction allegedly caused by doctors negligence.    
	Shilpi Bangals father said they ignored his complaints when she first developed blisters. The hospital denied any neglect but said Shilpis condition was critical.        
	Calcutta: Police raids to track down Pintu and his men, who had shot at their rivals on the busy Sambhunath Pandit Street on Friday afternoon injuring three, have drawn a blank. A dozen people have been detained because they know Pintu.        
	Krishnagar: A Class VII student was arrested on Saturday for beating up his headmaster. Joy-chand Roy had refused to promote him after he failed in four subjects.                                                                                                                                                                   
